data.text: @EU_Commission Per me è indifferente. Però, visto che con l'ora legale pare si risparmi, vorrei ricevere parte di quei risparmi.

@EU_Commission @EIB It could be better if you help by the same way the local organic farming to allow to improve the economy in the region everywhere in #EU. It's the moment to slow down the chemical and intensive agriculture which employ only few workers, impoverish the soils Kill the biodiversity
@EU_Commission Assolutamente no, si può mettere una via di mezzo tra le due? Ad ottobre dovremmo spostare indietro di un'ora ma la spostiamo indietro di mezz'ora soltanto e la lasciamo ferma così 😉
@EU_Commission When can this endless senseless debate be brought to an end?
@EU_Commission @EIB گود لاك يورو
@EU_Commission @EIB Facebook NELSON Lariccia mrNelson1963 @nelsonlariccia5 @nelsonlariccia
@EU_Commission Assolutamente NO
@EU_Commission Rester à l’heure d’été toute l’année svp
@EU_Commission Interference from the eu AGAIN ! LEAVE OUR TIME ALONE !!!!!!
@EU_Commission ma vi è realmente bisogno di fesserie come questa?
@EU_Commission È una delle poche cose utili : giù le mani dall’ora legale !!  Incomincio davvero a pensare che questo modo di fare Europa ...

@EU_Commission Engineering perspective: removing DST will be a programming nightmare causing major bugs in important software. Science perspective: there is evidence that DST directly causes friction in the economy and even fatalities due to coping problems. Make an informed decision.
@EU_Commission A time change twice a year is fine if the outcome is economy in energy consumption.
@EU_Commission Erasmus has provided our school IES Eduardo Pondal of Ponteceso with an opportunity for students to learn in non-formal situations. We do appreciate it.
@EU_Commission Yes
@EU_Commission For sure because Hungary stands up against the stupid EU
@EU_Commission Sommerzeit abschaffen !!!!!!!
@EU_Commission Vraag eens of men de EU wil afschaffen. Vind het vermoorden van de democratie door de EU  belangrijker dan zomer/wintertijd.

@EU_Commission #TimeforChange

Excuse me @EU_Commission, @EUCouncil, @coe and @Europarl_EN

Please can you advise me of the names of the candidates standing to replace @JunckerEU as President of the European Commission next year?

I would also like to see their manifestos if possible.
@EU_Commission No.
@EU_Commission zostawmy czas letni, i tak w Polsce zbyt szybko się ściemnia...
@EU_Commission Il n y a pas d autres problèmes à gérer en Europe bien sur... A quand le grand nettoyage de tous ces incapables?
@EU_Commission @MalmstromEU @Trade_EU @EBrivioEU This looks promising, disgraced @LiamFox ...

Happy #InternationalFriendshipDay to all people worldwide, not just those that are controlled by the #EUSSR
@EU_Commission Its a very bad idea if EU has to go global modernly. Because as time & seasons follow singular universal graticules & latitudinal paradigmal negligible +- M.000046 shift.
@EU_Commission Non
@EU_Commission @WWWednesdayLPL Keep summer time
@EU_Commission I Will always prefer summertime. ....
@EU_Commission Please stop the madness! I doubt we need daylight saving any longer.
@EU_Commission DST is a waste of time (pardon the pun) there shouldn't be any switching at all, especially considering not every country does it, and those that do don't do it at the same time.

@EU_Commission @MalmstromEU @Trade_EU @EBrivioEU Europe trading with the rest of the world?I hope Brexiteer eejits take note-and it's all because they are protecting their tax evasion/avoidance/ tax havens from the EU 2019 legislation which will clamp down on all these schemes.We are being played as fools.Scotland -Indyref asap
@EU_Commission Le changement d heure n est plus justifié. Restons a l heure d ete. Faut savoir sortir de ce qui est devenue une gêne pour tous. Faites le et arrêter de nous le demander tous les ans.
@EU_Commission Stop it, it's from another time
@EU_Commission Do not chang the clock twice a year.
@EU_Commission Useless and frustrating.
@EU_Commission End it an hour ago.
@EU_Commission Тц !
@EU_Commission I for one got used to the twice a year change, but it may have outlived its usefulness
@EU_Commission No more daylight savings.
@EU_Commission Except for Britain.......
@EU_Commission No. Enough of this!

@EU_Commission No! It's wonderful that I can work in Serbia in the same timezone as my colleagues in Brussels. It's great that I can tell almost anyone "11:00 CET," and we don't have to convert anything.
